liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: No late changes tonight. A big in and a big out for Collingwood, with Nick Daicos playing his first game since round 21 and Taylor Adams missing out due to an injury suffered at training. The Giants are unchanged from the team that beat Port Adelaide last weekend — what a luxury at this stage of the season. The subs are Jack Ginnivan for Collingwood and Xavier O'Halloran for GWS.
